    "The function f (ω q) is a real and dimensionless quantity that expresses the frequency dependence of the magnon density states.To arrive at Eq.",
    "(B5a) and Eq.",
    "(B5b), we assumed the rotating-wave approximation (RWA) [92], which neglects rapidly oscillating counter-rotating terms.",
    "Now, at short times (|ω q -ω 0 |t ≪ 1), if we consider |ω q -ω 0 | > γ, we can expand the exponential factor in Eq.",
    "(B5a) in a Taylor series in γ."
